body:
Found this interesting issue that has showed up in 0d48f71a6, which makes `firtool --ir-fir` drop location information from `firtool.instance` ops. Consider the following input:

```mlir
#locA = loc("fileA":42:1)
#locB = loc("fileB":9001:1)
firrtl.circuit "Foo" {
  firrtl.extmodule @Bar()
  firrtl.module @Foo() {
    firrtl.instance bar @Bar() loc(#locB)
  } loc(#locA)
}
```

Running this through `firtool --ir-fir` before 0d48f71a6 keeps the instance's location at `fileB:9001:1`. After 0d48f71a6, the instance drops its old location and inherits the parent module's location `fileA:42`.
